<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="149" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="149.[128,657,1065,1763]" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">
IDENTIFICATION: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[347,573,1124,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abrasus">
<emphasis box="[347,573,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">Molossops abrasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily identified by size and other morphological traits from other members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[128,251,1212,1235]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cynomops">
<emphasis box="[128,251,1212,1235]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">Cynomops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(tables 60, 61). Four subspecies are currently recognized (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, S. L. &amp; H. H. Genoways" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="213 - 236" part="49" refId="ref102406" refString="Williams, S. L., and H. H. Genoways 1980 a. Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 49: 213 - 236." title="Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1980">Williams and Genoways, 1980a</bibRefCitation>
; Koopman, 1994): 
<emphasis box="[527,551,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[568,583,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">mastivus</emphasis>
(Venezuela and the Guianas), 
<emphasis box="[539,563,1300,1323]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[577,592,1300,1323]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachymeles">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">brachymeles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(eastern Peru), 
<emphasis box="[422,446,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[462,477,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[492,584,1329,1352]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abrasus">
<emphasis box="[492,584,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">abrasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(eastern Brazil), and 
<emphasis box="[318,342,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[357,372,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[387,482,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">cerastes</emphasis>
(Paraguay and northern Argentina). These taxa are distinguished principally on the basis of size, with 
<emphasis box="[128,230,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">mastivus</emphasis>
being the largest (Goodwin, 1958; 
<bibRefCitation author="Taddei, V. A. &amp; L. D. Vizotto &amp; S. M. Martins" box="[128,350,1476,1499]" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="61 - 69" part="2" refId="ref100758" refString="Taddei, V. A., L. D. Vizotto, S. M. Martins 1976. Notas taxonomicas e biologicas sobre Molossops brachymeles cerastes (Thomas, 1901) (Chiroptera-Molossidae). Naturalia 2: 61 - 69." title="Notas taxonomicas e biologicas sobre Molossops brachymeles cerastes (Thomas, 1901) (Chiroptera-Molossidae)" type="journal article" year="1976">Taddei et al., 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, S. L. &amp; H. H. Genoways" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="213 - 236" part="49" refId="ref102406" refString="Williams, S. L., and H. H. Genoways 1980 a. Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 49: 213 - 236." title="Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1980">Williams and Genoways, 1980a</bibRefCitation>
, 1980b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="149.[128,657,1065,1763]" lastBlockId="149.[704,1233,845,1161]" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">
Our Paracou voucher, apparently the first record from French Guiana, conforms to previous qualitative descriptions of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1827" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abrasus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">Molossops abrasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and falls within the range of size variation previously reported for the species (Goodwin, 1958; 
<bibRefCitation author="Taddei, V. A. &amp; L. D. Vizotto &amp; S. M. Martins" box="[347,586,1681,1704]" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="61 - 69" part="2" refId="ref100758" refString="Taddei, V. A., L. D. Vizotto, S. M. Martins 1976. Notas taxonomicas e biologicas sobre Molossops brachymeles cerastes (Thomas, 1901) (Chiroptera-Molossidae). Naturalia 2: 61 - 69." title="Notas taxonomicas e biologicas sobre Molossops brachymeles cerastes (Thomas, 1901) (Chiroptera-Molossidae)" type="journal article" year="1976">Taddei et al., 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, S. L. &amp; H. H. Genoways" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="213 - 236" part="49" refId="ref102406" refString="Williams, S. L., and H. H. Genoways 1980 a. Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 49: 213 - 236." title="Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1980">Williams and Genoways, 1980a</bibRefCitation>
, 1980b; Koopman, 1994). Our specimen, a female, is somewhat smaller than a male identified as 
<emphasis box="[704,728,875,898]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[746,761,875,898]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[778,880,875,898]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">mastivus</emphasis>
that 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, S. L. &amp; H. H. Genoways" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="213 - 236" part="49" refId="ref102406" refString="Williams, S. L., and H. H. Genoways 1980 a. Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 49: 213 - 236." title="Results of the Alcoa Foundation-Suriname Expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1980">Williams and Genoways (1980a)</bibRefCitation>
reported from Surinam, but this difference is of the same magnitude as the sexual dimorphism that 
<bibRefCitation author="Taddei, V. A. &amp; L. D. Vizotto &amp; S. M. Martins" box="[946,1173,962,985]" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" pagination="61 - 69" part="2" refId="ref100758" refString="Taddei, V. A., L. D. Vizotto, S. M. Martins 1976. Notas taxonomicas e biologicas sobre Molossops brachymeles cerastes (Thomas, 1901) (Chiroptera-Molossidae). Naturalia 2: 61 - 69." title="Notas taxonomicas e biologicas sobre Molossops brachymeles cerastes (Thomas, 1901) (Chiroptera-Molossidae)" type="journal article" year="1976">Taddei et al. (1976)</bibRefCitation>
documented in a collection of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[1031,1165,992,1015]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abrasus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1055,992,1015]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1073,1165,992,1015]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="149">abrasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from eastern Brazil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
